article.headline: Nevada 92, S. Dakota St. 72
article.story: RENO, Nev. -- Brandon Fields scored 20 points to lead Nevada past South Dakota State 92-72 Saturday night. Armon Johnson scored 17 points and Luke Babbitt added 16 points and 10 rebounds as the Wolf Pack (4-4) remained unbeaten at home this season (4-0). Garrett Callahan and Nate Wolters each scored 15 points to lead South Dakota State (4-6). Garrett Callahan hit 3 of 5 3-pointers for nine points. Nevada, which has now won its last two games, took a 49-31 lead at the half. Fields scored 13 points and Joey Shaw had 10 of there points in the first. Fields scored 11 points in a span of 3:30 as Nevada took a 36-14 lead with 7:15 to go in the opening half. South Dakota State's Griffan Callahan hit a pair of 3-pointers in the final two minutes of the first half for his only six points of the game.
